My apologies, I seem to have provided incorrect information. It's possible you've accidentally turned on the display of non-printing characters in Word. These symbols indicate formatting marks like paragraph breaks, spaces, and tabs.

Here's how to turn them off:

Go to the Home tab.
In the Paragraph group, look for a small button that looks like a paragraph symbol (¶).
Click this button to toggle the display of non-printing characters on and off.
If you've accidentally added extra line breaks or paragraph marks, you can remove them using the Find and Replace function:

Go to the Home tab and click Replace (or use the keyboard shortcut Ctrl+H).
In the Find what field, type ^p^p (without quotes). This will find instances of two consecutive paragraph breaks.
Leave the Replace with field empty.
Click Replace All.
This will remove any extra line breaks and bring your text back to normal.

