How can I rotate a PDF with a free solution?



There are several free solutions available to rotate a PDF, both online and offline:

Online Tools (No Software Installation Required):

These are generally the quickest and easiest options for occasional use.

Smallpdf: (https://smallpdf.com/rotate-pdf)
Easy to use, just upload your PDF and use the rotate icons.
Allows rotation of individual pages or the entire file.
No signup is needed.
iLovePDF: (https://www.ilovepdf.com/rotate_pdf)
Allows you to rotate individual pages or all pages.
You can also rotate multiple PDF files at once.
PDF2Go: (https://www.pdf2go.com/rotate-pdf)
Displays pages as thumbnails for easy selection.
Offers options to rotate all pages or individual ones.
Supports uploading from your computer, Dropbox, Google Drive, or via a link.
Xodo: (https://xodo.com/rotate-pdf)
Allows rotation of specific pages or the entire document.
All processing is done on your device, so no files are uploaded to their server.
Sejda PDF: (https://www.sejda.com/rotate-pdf-pages)
Offers options to rotate all pages, only odd, or only even pages.
Allows rotation of specific pages.
PDF Converter: (https://www.freepdfconvert.com/rotate-pdf)
Simple interface to upload and rotate pages.
Claims to delete files automatically for privacy.
MaxAI: (https://www.maxai.co/pdf-tools/rotate-pdf/)
User-friendly interface for rotating specific or all pages.
Processes files in-browser for security.
PDFChef: (https://www.pdfchef.com/rotate-pdf.html)
Allows rotation of entire PDFs or individual pages.
Offers left, right, and 180° rotation.
Free Software (Install on your Computer):

These offer more features and can be used offline.

PDF24 Creator: (https://tools.pdf24.org/es/girar-pdf) (https://pdf24.org/en/creator)
A comprehensive free PDF tool that includes a rotate function.
Available for Windows. They also have online tools.
PDFsam Basic: (https://pdfsam.org/rotate-pdf/)
Free and open-source tool for Windows, Mac, and Linux.
Allows you to select specific pages or ranges to rotate.
Rotate PDF (Microsoft Store): (https://www.microsoft.com/en-ly/p/rotate-pdf/9pbcm58bsx84)
A simple and lightweight app for Windows.
PDF Rotator: (https://pdf-rotator.en.softonic.com/)
A dedicated free software for Windows specifically for rotating PDF files.
PDFgear: (https://pdfgear.com/)
Offers a free PDF editor for Windows and Mac with a rotate tool. They also have an online version.
Using a PDF Reader (for viewing, might not permanently save):

Some PDF readers like Adobe Acrobat Reader (free version) and others allow you to rotate the view of the PDF, but this might not permanently save the rotation. Look for a "Save As" option after rotating if you want to keep the changes.

Adobe Acrobat Reader:
Open the PDF.
Go to View > Rotate View and select Clockwise or Counterclockwise.
To save permanently, you might need to use their online service or a paid version.
Other PDF Readers: Many other free PDF readers have similar view rotation options. Check their "View" or "Page" menus.
In summary, for a free solution to rotate a PDF, your best options are usually the online tools for quick and easy rotation without installing software. If you need to do this frequently or want more features, a free software application like PDF24 Creator or PDFsam Basic would be a good choice.


